[assistant] Fixed the `Unrecognized calling convention: 63` failure and amended the existing commit.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause:
[assistant] - `Kernel32` extends JNA’s Win32/stdcall conventions.
[assistant] - On non-Windows, the temporary `kernel32` test library is a normal C shared library, so JNA’s stdcall convention was rejected.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change made:
[assistant] - On non-Windows, before `ObjectFactory` initializes `Kernel32`, the test now temporarily overrides `W32APIOptions.DEFAULT_OPTIONS` to use JNA’s C calling convention for the test JVM.
[assistant] - The minimal generated `kernel32` test library remains responsible for providing `GetUserDefaultLCID`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated file:
[assistant] - `tests/src/net.java.dev.jna/jna-platform/5.8.0/src/test/java/net_java_dev_jna/jna_platform/ObjectFactoryTest.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Commit amended:
[assistant] - `a39ac516d1 Add ObjectFactory dynamic proxy coverage for jna-platform`
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run the Gradle test locally.
