[assistant] Fixed the latest JNA callback/calling-convention failure and amended the existing commit.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause:
[assistant] - The previous in-memory dispatch used JNA `DispatchListener`, whose callback vtable uses Win32/stdcall callbacks.
[assistant] - On Linux, JNA rejects that callback calling convention (`Invalid calling convention 63`).
[assistant] 
[assistant] Change made:
[assistant] - Removed the Java callback-backed `DispatchListener` test double.
[assistant] - The test now builds a tiny native test library that provides:
[assistant]   - `GetUserDefaultLCID` for `ObjectFactory` static initialization on non-Windows.
[assistant]   - A minimal COM-like `IDispatch` vtable implemented in C for `AddRef`, `Release`, and `QueryInterface`.
[assistant] - `ObjectFactory.createProxy(...)` now receives a real JNA `Dispatch` backed by native memory, avoiding unsupported Java callback conventions.
[assistant] - Added native-image reflection metadata for `W32APIOptions.DEFAULT_OPTIONS`, which the test adjusts on non-Windows to use C calling convention for the fake native library.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated files:
[assistant] - `tests/src/net.java.dev.jna/jna-platform/5.8.0/src/test/java/net_java_dev_jna/jna_platform/ObjectFactoryTest.java`
[assistant] - `tests/src/net.java.dev.jna/jna-platform/5.8.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/jna-platform-test/reflect-config.json`
[assistant] - `tests/src/net.java.dev.jna/jna-platform/5.8.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/jna-platform-test/proxy-config.json`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Commit amended:
[assistant] - `4dbf3146f4 Add ObjectFactory dynamic proxy coverage for jna-platform`
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run the Gradle test locally.
[assistant-event] text_end
